CORELLI: Buonasera, signorina

606
00:44:33,107 --> 00:44:35,338
Are you going to shoot me?

607
00:44:52,508 --> 00:44:53,782
PELAGIA: It wasn't loaded.

608
00:45:02,110 --> 00:45:06,148
I've never aimed a gun
at anybody.

609
00:45:06,229 --> 00:45:07,821
Never in my life.

610
00:45:11,150 --> 00:45:12,583
CORELLI:
It must be very difficult...

611
00:45:12,670 --> 00:45:15,343
for you to have
to put up with us.

612
00:45:15,430 --> 00:45:16,580
It must be very difficult...

613
00:45:16,671 --> 00:45:19,583
for you to have
to live with yourself.

614
00:45:19,671 --> 00:45:23,219
You lie in the sun
and swim in the sea...

615
00:45:23,310 --> 00:45:26,348
and flirt with your prostitutes.

616
00:45:26,431 --> 00:45:30,390
And there are people I know,
people I grew up with...

617
00:45:30,471 --> 00:45:32,269
who are fighting
for their lives...

618
00:45:32,352 --> 00:45:34,990
and dying for what
they believe in.

619
00:45:35,071 --> 00:45:36,743
And all you do is sing.

620
00:45:40,752 --> 00:45:42,390
What's there to sing about?

621
00:45:42,472 --> 00:45:47,593
We are in the middle of a war,
not an opera house.

622
00:45:47,673 --> 00:45:49,663
And you, you think
you are so cultured...

623
00:45:49,752 --> 00:45:51,743
with your pasta
and your panettone...

624
00:45:51,832 --> 00:45:53,391
and your puffed-up opera.

625
00:45:56,353 --> 00:45:59,346
Why don't you take your holiday
on somebody else's island?

626
00:46:04,073 --> 00:46:05,904
What is there to sing about?

627
00:46:07,834 --> 00:46:10,712
There is singing
when babies are baptised...

628
00:46:10,794 --> 00:46:15,505
when you celebrate a marriage.

629
00:46:15,595 --> 00:46:17,585
Men sing as they work.

630
00:46:17,674 --> 00:46:22,066
Soldiers sing
as they march into battle...

631
00:46:22,155 --> 00:46:27,275
and there is singing
when people die.

632
00:46:27,355 --> 00:46:30,189
I have always found something
in life worth singing about...

633
00:46:31,755 --> 00:46:35,066
and for that
I cannot apologise.

634
00:46:39,716 --> 00:46:42,106
For the fact that
I've caused you pain...

635
00:46:42,197 --> 00:46:45,428
I cannot apologise enough.

636
00:46:45,516 --> 00:46:50,716
I have not been able
to imagine, until now...

637
00:46:50,797 --> 00:46:53,311
the offence I have given.

638
00:47:04,038 --> 00:47:05,994
[Playing]

639
00:47:29,399 --> 00:47:31,469
-What are those?
-My things.

640
00:47:31,559 --> 00:47:34,552
IANNIS: I can see that. Why?

641
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:37,677
CORELLI: I'm going to stay
in the encampment with my men.

642
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:39,194
I think it will be best.

643
00:47:39,281 --> 00:47:40,555
IANNIS:
But you must understand...

644
00:47:40,641 --> 00:47:42,949
I made an arrangement
with your quartermaster.

645
00:47:43,040 --> 00:47:44,758
We agreed the terms.

646
00:47:44,840 --> 00:47:47,309
I would not feel comfortable...

647
00:47:47,401 --> 00:47:49,471
Letting him down.

648
00:47:49,561 --> 00:47:53,635
Therefore,
I think you should stay.

649
00:47:53,722 --> 00:47:57,555
CORELLI: I don't think
your daughter would agree.

650
00:47:57,641 --> 00:47:59,791
My daughter
understands the importance...

651
00:47:59,881 --> 00:48:01,201
of honouring an arrangement.

652
00:48:01,282 --> 00:48:03,159
I'll speak to the quartermaster.

653
00:48:03,242 --> 00:48:06,359
Make sure you continue
to get your medical supplies.

654
00:48:06,442 --> 00:48:09,594
I've enjoyed meeting you.

655
00:48:09,683 --> 00:48:11,559
I'm only sorry
about the circumstances.

656
00:48:11,642 --> 00:48:13,598
