-Advantages?

777
01:00:10,053 --> 01:00:11,566
CORELLI: The advantage
of thinking that...

778
01:00:11,653 --> 01:00:13,644
other races
are inferior to yours.

779
01:00:13,733 --> 01:00:15,052
It's a question of science.

780
01:00:15,133 --> 01:00:16,806
You can't alter
a scientific fact.

781
01:00:16,894 --> 01:00:18,486
I don't care about science.

782
01:00:18,574 --> 01:00:20,450
It's morality that counts.

783
01:00:20,533 --> 01:00:21,761
What is your morality?

784
01:00:21,853 --> 01:00:23,003
CORELLI:
If I were to see a man...

785
01:00:23,094 --> 01:00:24,573
being set upon by others...

786
01:00:24,654 --> 01:00:26,645
I would think
that man was my brother.

787
01:00:26,734 --> 01:00:28,167
That is my morality.

788
01:00:28,254 --> 01:00:30,689
I would make myself
believe it's personal.

789
01:00:30,775 --> 01:00:33,005
For me, too,
the war is personal.

790
01:00:33,095 --> 01:00:35,164
I lost both my grandfathers
in the Great War.

791
01:00:35,254 --> 01:00:36,812
MAN: A war that you started.

792
01:00:36,894 --> 01:00:38,044
WEBER:
And my father's brother...

793
01:00:38,135 --> 01:00:39,727
two of my mother's brothers.

794
01:00:39,815 --> 01:00:43,046
I grew up in a country
where it was hard to survive.

795
01:00:43,135 --> 01:00:45,172
We were hungry all the time.

796
01:00:45,256 --> 01:00:47,724
All we ever knew about
was defeat. But now--

797
01:00:47,816 --> 01:00:49,214
IANNIS:
Sometimes it is better...

798
01:00:49,295 --> 01:00:53,209
to lose than to have
so much blood on your hands.

799
01:00:53,296 --> 01:00:54,490
SOLDIER:
It's a beautiful night...

800
01:00:54,576 --> 01:00:56,487
and everything is peaceful...

801
01:00:56,576 --> 01:00:59,967
and we should think
about falling in love.

802
01:01:00,057 --> 01:01:02,013
[People laugh and chatter]

803
01:01:06,897 --> 01:01:08,853
[Corelli plays mandolin]

804
01:02:43,783 --> 01:02:45,136
[Song ends]

805
01:02:49,504 --> 01:02:51,540
That's beautiful.

806
01:02:51,624 --> 01:02:52,978
What is it?

807
01:02:54,265 --> 01:02:56,142
It's "Pelagia's Song."

808
01:03:23,507 --> 01:03:25,224
[Birds chirping]

809
01:03:28,947 --> 01:03:30,903
[Motorcycle engine rattles]

810
01:03:51,589 --> 01:03:54,022
I wrote you that song
because I love you.

811
01:03:56,188 --> 01:03:58,703
I don't care
if the world knows it.

812
01:04:00,909 --> 01:04:02,103
I couldn't care less...

813
01:04:02,189 --> 01:04:04,784
if I never pick up
the mandolin again.

814
01:04:04,870 --> 01:04:09,226
When I was playing, it felt like
my hands were lumps of wood.

815
01:04:10,509 --> 01:04:15,300
It felt as if every note
was sour, stale.

816
01:04:17,870 --> 01:04:20,749
And then I realised--

817
01:04:20,831 --> 01:04:23,503
it's useless.

818
01:04:23,590 --> 01:04:25,387
It's hopeless.

819
01:04:26,871 --> 01:04:30,705
It can't begin to express
the way I feel about you.

820
01:04:36,192 --> 01:04:37,749
[Breathing deeply]

821
01:05:53,517 --> 01:05:55,075
IANNIS:
Next time you see him...

822
01:05:55,157 --> 01:05:57,432
tell him I have got
his mandolin.

823
01:06:00,118 --> 01:06:02,267
He left it in the square.

824
01:06:12,438 --> 01:06:14,191
[Birds chirping]

825
01:06:32,439 --> 01:06:36,877
Four more boys from the village
have left to join Mandras.

826
01:06:38,760 --> 01:06:41,355
Constantine's boys.

827
01:06:41,441 --> 01:06:43,591
Kostas's brother,
what's his name?

828
01:06:43,681 --> 01:06:45,238
George.

829
01:06:45,320 --> 01:06:48,916
He's only fifteen.

830
01:06:49,001 --> 01:06:51,037
He always worshipped Mandras.

831
01:06:52,521 --> 01:06:53,795
Do you love him?

832
01:06:55,001 --> 01:06:56,833
We are engaged to be married.

833
01:06:58,322 --> 01:07:00,277
I am not talking about Mandras.

834
01:07:12,683 --> 01:07:14,513
IANNIS:
When you fall in love...

835
01:07:14,602 --> 01:07:18,755
it is a temporary madness.

836
01:07:18,843 --> 01:07:23,678
It erupts like an earthquake,
and then it subsides.

837
01:07:23,763 --> 01:07:27,518
And when it subsides,
you have to make a decision.

838
01:07:27,604 --> 01:07:30,675
You have to work out
whether your roots...

839
01:07:30,763 --> 01:07:32,277
have become
so entwined together...

840
01:07:32,364 --> 01:07:34,082
that it is inconceivable...

841
01:07:34,164 --> 01:07:36,120
that you should ever part.

842
01:07:37,684 --> 01:07:41,803
Because this is what love is.

843
01:07:46,005 --> 01:07:49,361
Love is not breathlessness.
It is not excitement.

844
01:07:49,445 --> 01:07:52,278
It's not the desire to mate
every second of the day.

845
01:07:52,365 --> 01:07:53,845
It is not lying awake
at night...

846
01:07:53,926 --> 01:07:57,315
imagining that he is kissing
every part of your body.

847
01:08:01,086 --> 01:08:04,556
No, don't blush.

848
01:08:08,007 --> 01:08:10,077
I'm telling you some truths.

849
01:08:12,526 --> 01:08:14,757
That is just being in love...

850
01:08:14,847 --> 01:08:19,602
which any of us
can convince ourselves we are.

851
01:08:19,687 --> 01:08:23,363
Love itself
is what is left over...

852
01:08:23,448 --> 01:08:26,405
when being in love
has burned away.

853
01:08:28,368 --> 01:08:31,007
Doesn't sound very exciting,
does it?

854
01:08:31,088 --> 01:08:32,316
[Chuckles]

855
01:08:34,528 --> 01:08:36,042
But it is.

856
01:08:39,448 --> 01:08:42,919
Do you think that you
could begin to imagine...

857
01:08:43,009 --> 01:08:46,160
that that is how you will come
to feel with Captain Corelli?

858
01:08:54,849 --> 01:08:56,123
Pelagia...

859
01:08:58,010 --> 01:09:00,478
You must act honourably...

860
01:09:00,570 --> 01:09:03,926
with respect
to Mandras and his mother.

861
01:09:07,850 --> 01:09:09,249
And...

862
01:09:11,090 --> 01:09:14,766
pray for the liberation
of the island...

863
01:09:14,851 --> 01:09:19,130
because then everything
becomes possible.

864
01:09:21,012 --> 01:09:21,364
[Children chatter]

865
01:10:13,455 --> 01:10:14,808
Drosoula.

866
01:10:17,096 --> 01:10:19,325
All night I've been thinking
about Mandras.

867
01:10:21,295 --> 01:10:22,775
About me and Mandras.

868
01:10:24,776 --> 01:10:27,415
Thinking about how long
we've been apart.

869
01:10:40,457 --> 01:10:42,732
When did you arrive?

870
01:10:42,817 --> 01:10:44,171
Where is your ring?

871
01:10:46,178 --> 01:10:47,974
My fingers got too thin.

872
01:10:50,537 --> 01:10:52,051
I thought I would lose it.

873
01:10:56,538 --> 01:10:57,766
Where will you stay?

874
01:10:57,858 --> 01:10:59,372
I want to ask you something.

875
01:11:01,659 --> 01:11:03,853
We need to see
the Italian captain.

876
01:11:05,298 --> 01:11:08,450
I want you to ask him
to meet with us.

877
01:11:08,539 --> 01:11:10,928
As soon as you can.

878
01:11:11,019 --> 01:11:12,851
RADIO: In Germany,
the port of Hamburg...

879
01:11:12,940 --> 01:11:15,374
suffered a second day
of continuous air raids...

880
01:11:15,460 --> 01:11:17,768
from nearly
800 British aircraft...

881
01:11:17,859 --> 01:11:20,010
Leaving much of the city
in ruin.

882
01:11:20,100 --> 01:11:22,614
While, in ltaly,
Rome has finally fallen...

883
01:11:22,700 --> 01:11:25,533
to the Allied advance after
weeks of fierce fighting...

884
01:11:25,620 --> 01:11:28,215
and a huge bombing campaign
on the capital.

885
01:11:28,301 --> 01:11:29,893
Allied commandos...

886
01:11:29,981 --> 01:11:32,210
are closely watching
the Mediterranean countries...

887
01:11:32,300 --> 01:11:34,451
occupied by German
and Italian forces.

888
01:11:34,541 --> 01:11:37,499
It's not yet clear
what the German attitude...

889
01:11:37,581 --> 01:11:39,458
to an Italian withdrawal
might be...

890
01:11:39,541 --> 01:11:41,453
but Germany
will assume sole command...

891
01:11:41,542 --> 01:11:43,737
of many strategic territories.

892
01:11:43,822 --> 01:11:47,211
Hitler is expected to send
massive reinforcements...

893
01:11:47,301 --> 01:11:49,452
through the Balkans
and into Greece...

894
01:11:49,542 --> 01:11:52,010
as the Nazis struggle
to maintain supply routes...

895
01:11:52,102 --> 01:11:53,296
to northern Africa.

896
01:11:54,342 --> 01:11:55,742
Mandras is back.

897
01:11:55,823 --> 01:11:57,620
He wants to see you.

898
01:11:57,703 --> 01:11:59,658
[Engine revs]

899
01:11:59,742 --> 01:12:01,653
La donna è mobile

900
01:12:01,742 --> 01:12:03,654
Qual piuma al vento

901
01:12:03,743 --> 01:12:07,452
Muta d'accento

902
01:12:07,543 --> 01:12:09,135
E di pensiero

903
01:12:09,223 --> 01:12:11,021
It's over! It's all over!

904
01:12:11,104 --> 01:12:12,935
-Mussolini has fallen!
-Finito!

905
01:12:13,024 --> 01:12:14,217
We're going home!

906
01:12:14,303 --> 01:12:15,531
Finito!

907
01:12:15,623 --> 01:12:17,580
[Shouting and chattering]

908
01:12:18,704 --> 01:12:20,456
[Speaking Italian]

909
01:12:20,544 --> 01:12:22,500
[Bell ringing]

910
01:12:24,745 --> 01:12:26,701
[Shouting and chattering]

911
01:12:36,665 --> 01:12:39,021
[Ringing]

912
01:12:39,106 --> 01:12:41,062
[Bells chiming]

913
01:12:42,665 --> 01:12:44,621
[Shouting and chattering]

914
01:12:49,026 --> 01:12:50,982
[Villagers applauding
and cheering]

915
01:13:11,707 --> 01:13:13,663
[Applause and cheering]

916
01:13:20,228 --> 01:13:23,426
Colonel Barge and I have agreed
the date for the surrender...

917
01:13:23,509 --> 01:13:25,817
of our heavy weapons
and machine guns--

918
01:13:25,908 --> 01:13:28,139
the fifteenth of September.

919
01:13:28,229 --> 01:13:30,026
That's in five days time.

920
01:13:31,829 --> 01:13:34,423
CAPTAIN: Why should we
lay down our arms?

921
01:13:34,509 --> 01:13:36,421
They were our allies.

922
01:13:36,510 --> 01:13:39,387
Why should they be
dictating terms to us?

923
01:13:39,469 --> 01:13:41,027
We have surrendered.

924
01:13:41,109 --> 01:13:44,420
Mussolini has surrendered to
the British and the Americans...

925
01:13:44,510 --> 01:13:45,943
not to the Germans.

926
01:13:46,030 --> 01:13:48,908
GANDIN: Colonel Barge
and I have agreed.

927
01:13:48,990 --> 01:13:53,506
If we surrender our arms,
do we have confirmation...

928
01:13:53,590 --> 01:13:55,979
that they will not
use force against us?

929
01:13:56,070 --> 01:13:57,390
GANDIN: I have
a personal undertaking...

930
01:13:57,471 --> 01:13:58,790
from Colonel Barge
and his officers...

931
01:13:58,871 --> 01:14:00,862
that our troops
will be allowed safe passage.

932
01:14:00,951 --> 01:14:02,748
CAPTAIN: My men will
never agree to return home...

933
01:14:02,831 --> 01:14:04,390
without their weapons.

934
01:14:04,472 --> 01:14:07,111
If you surrender your arms
in times of war...

935
01:14:07,192 --> 01:14:08,704
then you are no longer a man.

936
01:14:08,791 --> 01:14:10,110
GANDIN: If you were
in their position...

937
01:14:10,191 --> 01:14:11,591
if you were German...

938
01:14:11,672 --> 01:14:14,550
you would want to be certain
for your own security...

939
01:14:14,632 --> 01:14:16,429
that the weapons
will not be passed on...

940
01:14:16,512 --> 01:14:19,664
to the Allied forces
or to the Greek partisans.

941
01:14:19,753 --> 01:14:21,106
Or turned against you.

942
01:14:23,552 --> 01:14:25,589
Or turned against you.

943
01:14:27,433 --> 01:14:29,389
[Engine revs]

944
01:14:56,955 --> 01:14:59,947
You must be looking forward
to going home.

945
01:15:00,035 --> 01:15:03,711
There'll be people happy
to see you again, I'm sure.

946
01:15:03,796 --> 01:15:07,105
Your family, your mother,
your wife.

947
01:15:07,195 --> 01:15:08,424
Your girlfriend?

948
01:15:09,956 --> 01:15:11,708
CORELLI: You wanted to see me?

949
01:15:11,796 --> 01:15:13,275
MANDRAS: We need arms.

950
01:15:13,356 --> 01:15:16,030
Machine guns,
ammunition, land mines...

951
01:15:16,117 --> 01:15:17,630
anything you can spare.

952
01:15:17,717 --> 01:15:19,468
How can I give you weapons?

953
01:15:19,556 --> 01:15:22,024
-You know I can't do that.
-You've surrendered.

954
01:15:22,116 --> 01:15:23,311
If you don't intend to fight...

955
01:15:23,397 --> 01:15:24,546
you won't be needing
your weapons.

956
01:15:24,637 --> 01:15:26,116
We have a country to defend.

957
01:15:26,197 --> 01:15:27,471
DIMITRIS:
There is a massive build up...

958
01:15:27,557 --> 01:15:29,468
of German troops
on the mainland.

959
01:15:29,558 --> 01:15:32,789
The 117th Jaeger Division
is nearing the Corinth Canal.

960
01:15:32,878 --> 01:15:35,710
The 104th is moving south
from Yugoslavia.

961
01:15:35,797 --> 01:15:38,028
Then you are not
in any position to resist.

962
01:15:38,118 --> 01:15:39,392
Unless we act now.

963
01:15:39,478 --> 01:15:42,629
Do you know, Captain,
on Lefkada island...

964
01:15:42,718 --> 01:15:44,232
all the Italians
who surrendered...

965
01:15:44,319 --> 01:15:47,197
have been sent
to prison camps in the north.

966
01:15:51,399 --> 01:15:53,117
We heard they went home.

967
01:15:53,199 --> 01:15:55,667
The trains were diverted
in Albania.

968
01:15:55,759 --> 01:15:57,909
MANDRAS:
In this war, Captain...

969
01:15:57,999 --> 01:16:00,355
it's hard to know
who you can trust.

970
01:16:00,440 --> 01:16:03,556
But one thing is certain--

971
01:16:03,639 --> 01:16:05,437
you can't trust the Germans.

972
01:16:09,120 --> 01:16:11,076
[Soldiers shouting]

973
01:16:16,320 --> 01:16:17,992
[Yells]

974
01:16:38,402 --> 01:16:40,120
Last night I dreamed
I was sitting...

975
01:16:40,202 --> 01:16:43,559
in a restaurant
in Piazza Navona...

976
01:16:43,643 --> 01:16:47,237
eating
zuppe di cozze piccante...

977
01:16:47,322 --> 01:16:50,235
then a plate
of tagliarini al boscaiolo.

978
01:16:57,124 --> 01:16:58,352
Colonel Barge has requested...

979
01:16:58,444 --> 01:17:01,435
I withdraw your battery
from Antisamos Beach.

980
01:17:04,324 --> 01:17:07,396
If they wanted to bring in
heavy reinforcements...

981
01:17:07,484 --> 01:17:10,636
this is where they would do it.

982
01:17:10,725 --> 01:17:12,397
Is this an order?

983
01:17:12,485 --> 01:17:14,042
Captain...

984
01:17:14,124 --> 01:17:16,080
don't you want to go home?

985
01:17:35,086 --> 01:17:37,042
[Vehicles rumbling]

986
01:18:08,889 --> 01:18:10,083
[German soldier yells]

987
01:18:17,769 --> 01:18:19,043
Are you going to let us through?

988
01:18:19,129 --> 01:18:20,528
My orders are to supervise...

989
01:18:20,609 --> 01:18:22,726
the surrender
of your arms and weapons.

990
01:18:23,770 --> 01:18:25,680
[Soldiers cocking guns]

991
01:18:31,330 --> 01:18:34,481
The deadline for the hand-over
is at noon tomorrow.

992
01:18:34,570 --> 01:18:36,243
WEBER: Antonio.

993
01:18:38,810 --> 01:18:41,722
This order comes
from Colonel Barge.

994
01:18:41,810 --> 01:18:43,130
He has asked me personally...

995
01:18:43,211 --> 01:18:45,486
to assure you that
if you surrender your arms...

996
01:18:45,571 --> 01:18:48,802
you will be guaranteed
safe passage.

997
01:18:48,891 --> 01:18:52,043
Like the Italian garrison
at Lefkada?

998
01:18:53,411 --> 01:18:55,641
Lefkada?

999
01:18:55,731 --> 01:18:57,962
But they laid down
their weapons.

1000
01:18:58,052 --> 01:18:59,280
They went home.

1001
01:19:20,134 --> 01:19:21,362
[Weapon thumps]

1002
01:19:26,054 --> 01:19:27,885
[Soldier shouts in German]

1003
01:19:27,974 --> 01:19:29,930
[Dropping weapons]

1004
01:19:36,934 --> 01:19:38,970
[Soldier yells in German]

1005
01:19:39,054 --> 01:19:42,092
You must be looking forward
to seeing ltaly again.

1006
01:19:45,375 --> 01:19:46,729
Do you think
we could keep in touch?

1007
01:19:49,056 --> 01:19:51,330
I mean, after the war,
of course.

1008
01:19:56,296 --> 01:19:58,252
[Soldiers speaking German]

1009
01:20:05,136 --> 01:20:08,288
You can have my gun when
I've finished my cigarette.

1010
01:20:12,977 --> 01:20:14,774
Get your hands off me, you ba--

1011
01:20:16,738 --> 01:20:18,693
[Gunfire and shouting]

1012
01:20:22,858 --> 01:20:24,814
[Soldiers shouting]

1013
01:20:32,459 --> 01:20:33,937
I understand your concern.

1014
01:20:34,018 --> 01:20:36,487
If I were in your shoes, I would
be asking questions, too.

1015
01:20:36,579 --> 01:20:38,490
Of course, we will
investigate what happened--

1016
01:20:38,579 --> 01:20:40,968
I can tell you
what happened--

1017
01:20:41,059 --> 01:20:42,208
My men are dead!

1018
01:20:42,299 --> 01:20:43,892
...take the appropriate action.

1019
01:20:43,980 --> 01:20:46,699
CORELLI: What does that mean?

1020
01:20:46,780 --> 01:20:50,408
Does it mean that I can write
to the families of these men...

1021
01:20:50,499 --> 01:20:52,855
and tell them that their
murderers will be charged...

1022
01:20:52,940 --> 01:20:54,453
that justice will prevail?

1023
01:20:54,540 --> 01:20:57,771
You force us at gunpoint to
line up and surrender our arms.

1024
01:20:57,861 --> 01:20:59,852
You impound our weapons.

1025
01:20:59,941 --> 01:21:01,215
We're supposed to be allies!

1026
01:21:01,301 --> 01:21:02,813
GANDIN:
Captain Corelli, please!

1027
01:21:04,340 --> 01:21:06,855
We need some kind of assurance.

1028
01:21:09,661 --> 01:21:12,256
I can assure you
that the order to disarm...

1029
01:21:12,342 --> 01:21:14,697
did not come
from my headquarters.

1030
01:21:17,581 --> 01:21:19,971
GANDIN: We have agreed to
the surrender of our arms...

1031
01:21:20,062 --> 01:21:21,575
by noon tomorrow.

1032
01:21:21,662 --> 01:21:24,574
We would like your assurance
that no more of our troops...

1033
01:21:24,662 --> 01:21:28,576
will be forcibly disarmed
before that deadline.

1034
01:21:28,663 --> 01:21:31,779
BARGE: Herr General,
by noon tomorrow...

1035
01:21:31,862 --> 01:21:35,253
I guarantee
you'll be on your way home.

1036
01:21:35,343 --> 01:21:36,537
[Clicks heels]

1037
01:21:51,144 --> 01:21:52,657
[Soldier speaking Italian]

1038
01:21:52,744 --> 01:21:55,578
QUARTERMASTER:
This is not our war.

1039
01:21:55,665 --> 01:21:57,781
This is between
the Greeks and the Germans.

1040
01:21:57,865 --> 01:22:00,332
CORELLI: Would you prefer we
left them to fight on their own?

1041
01:22:00,424 --> 01:22:02,222
[Sighs]

1042
01:22:02,305 --> 01:22:04,739
CORELLI: The 4th Regiment
will hold Antisamos.

1043
01:22:04,825 --> 01:22:07,055
We'll keep the 5th
in reserve at Assos...

1044
01:22:07,145 --> 01:22:09,614
and I will take
the 8th and 9th to Argostoli.

1045
01:22:12,506 --> 01:22:14,063
[Soldier speaking Italian]

1046
01:22:14,145 --> 01:22:15,817
CORELLI: All gun lines
to be in position...

1047
01:22:15,905 --> 01:22:17,817
by first light tomorrow.

1048
01:22:44,787 --> 01:22:46,540
[Trucks approaching]

1049
01:23:04,829 --> 01:23:06,468
If we resist now,
we can beat them.

1050
01:23:06,550 --> 01:23:08,461
What if the Germans send planes?

1051
01:23:08,550 --> 01:23:11,507
Don't go near Argostoli.
Stay away from Antisamos Beach.

1052
01:23:11,589 --> 01:23:14,058
I want to lie across the road
so that you can't leave.

1053
01:23:14,150 --> 01:23:17,108
Keep a gun with you
at all times. Promise me.

1054
01:23:19,470 --> 01:23:21,189
Come back to me.

1055
01:23:21,271 --> 01:23:22,670
Promise me.

1056
01:23:24,350 --> 01:23:25,863
[Panting]

1057
01:23:25,950 --> 01:23:29,546
When it's over,
you will come back to me.

1058
01:23:46,512 --> 01:23:48,070
[Jeep engine revs]

1059
01:23:52,153 --> 01:23:53,710
[Breathes heavily]

1060
01:23:56,232 --> 01:23:58,189
CARLO: I know what you feel.

1061
01:24:00,233 --> 01:24:03,191
You think if he died
your world will stop.

1062
01:24:05,154 --> 01:24:07,109
I will look out for him.

1063
01:24:15,554 --> 01:24:17,510
[Starts engine]

1064
01:24:36,275 --> 01:24:38,231
[Equipment rumbling]

1065
01:24:42,436 --> 01:24:43,630
[Soldier yells]

1066
01:24:47,517 --> 01:24:49,269
[Soldier speaking Italian]

1067
01:24:52,596 --> 01:24:54,269
[Boy speaking Italian]

1068
01:25:01,278 --> 01:25:02,711
[Clicking]

1069
01:25:12,958 --> 01:25:14,311
[Explosion]

1070
01:25:14,398 --> 01:25:16,355
[Buzzing]

1071
01:25:18,199 --> 01:25:19,551
[People yelling]

1072
01:25:29,240 --> 01:25:30,468
Pelagia!

1073
01:25:40,080 --> 01:25:41,274
[Bomb whistling]

1074
01:25:45,721 --> 01:25:47,312
[People chattering]

1075
01:25:49,800 --> 01:25:50,950
GIRL: Mama! Mama!

1076
01:25:51,041 --> 01:25:52,679
MANDRAS: Pelagia!

1077
01:25:52,761 --> 01:25:54,160
[Explosion]

1078
01:25:54,241 --> 01:25:56,436
Stay here! It's not safe!

1079
01:25:56,521 --> 01:25:57,955
[Girl screams]

1080
01:25:59,082 --> 01:26:00,595
Pelagia!

1081
01:26:00,682 --> 01:26:01,830
[People shouting]

1082
01:26:01,921 --> 01:26:03,513
[Children yelling]

1083
01:26:03,601 --> 01:26:05,558
[Gunfire]

1084
01:26:05,642 --> 01:26:06,995
[Yelling]

1085
01:26:09,842 --> 01:26:11,434
[Screaming and gunfire]

1086
01:26:11,522 --> 01:26:12,717
[Yells]

1087
01:26:16,922 --> 01:26:18,116
Drosoula!

1088
01:26:19,163 --> 01:26:20,994
ELENI: Drosoula!

1089
01:26:21,083 --> 01:26:24,280
-Drosoula! Drosoula!
-What are you doing?

1090
01:26:24,363 --> 01:26:27,674
-She's a traitor and a whore.
-Mandras.

1091
01:26:27,764 --> 01:26:30,436
ELENI: Help me! Help me!

1092
01:26:31,363 --> 01:26:32,512
Mandras.

1093
01:26:32,603 --> 01:26:34,435
ELENI: Help me!

1094
01:26:34,524 --> 01:26:35,718
[Woman screams]

1095
01:26:47,244 --> 01:26:49,201
[Gunfire]

1096
01:26:54,365 --> 01:26:55,879
[Gunfire]

1097
01:26:59,485 --> 01:27:00,634
[Bomb whistles]

1098
01:27:00,725 --> 01:27:02,444
[Explosion]

1099
01:27:08,886 --> 01:27:10,240
[Speaking Italian]

1100
01:27:11,887 --> 01:27:14,195
[Soldiers shouting]

1101
01:27:14,286 --> 01:27:15,480
[Woman yelling]

1102
01:27:15,566 --> 01:27:16,920
[Gunfire]

1103
01:27:20,367 --> 01:27:22,278
The enemy's
a hundred metres away.

1104
01:27:22,367 --> 01:27:23,960
There's heavy armour coming.

1105
01:27:24,048 --> 01:27:25,401
[Gunfire]

1106
01:27:28,967 --> 01:27:30,446
[Shouting]

1107
01:27:38,289 --> 01:27:39,483
[Yells]

1108
01:27:44,008 --> 01:27:45,362
[Gunfire]

1109
01:27:47,249 --> 01:27:49,683
[Soldier shouting in Italian]

1110
01:27:53,170 --> 01:27:54,728
[Soldier speaking German]

1111
01:28:00,410 --> 01:28:01,763
[Windows shatter]

1112
01:28:05,570 --> 01:28:07,004
[Grunts]

1113
01:28:14,451 --> 01:28:15,645
Aah!

1114
01:28:19,291 --> 01:28:20,566
Aah!

1115
01:28:25,171 --> 01:28:27,640
[Yelling]

1116
01:28:30,612 --> 01:28:31,806
[Soldiers shouting]

1117
01:28:34,132 --> 01:28:35,725
Aaah!

1118
01:28:38,612 --> 01:28:40,011
[Screaming]

1119
01:28:43,093 --> 01:28:45,129
[Screaming]

1120
01:28:45,213 --> 01:28:47,169
[Shouts in Italian]

1121
01:28:53,813 --> 01:28:55,166
[Gunfire]

1122
01:28:58,374 --> 01:28:59,648
[Shouting]

1123
01:29:07,894 --> 01:29:09,088
[Yelling]

1124
01:29:25,776 --> 01:29:27,732
[Men shouting]

1125
01:29:39,377 --> 01:29:41,333
[Soldier speaking German]

1126
01:29:45,777 --> 01:29:47,734
[Soldiers marching]

1127
01:31:01,262 --> 01:31:03,059
[Issuing orders in German]

1128
01:31:10,183 --> 01:31:12,140
[Soldier speaking German]

1129
01:31:19,944 --> 01:31:21,502
[Speaks German]

1130
01:31:42,346 --> 01:31:43,574
CORELLI: Gunther.

1131
01:31:58,027 --> 01:31:59,175
Gunther.

1132
01:31:59,266 --> 01:32:00,585
Come on, move!

1133
01:32:03,427 --> 01:32:05,383
[Truck engine starts]

1134
01:32:23,549 --> 01:32:25,505
[Praying in Italian]

1135
01:32:27,548 --> 01:32:28,822
[Screams]

1136
01:32:30,228 --> 01:32:32,106
[Gunshot]

1137
01:32:32,189 --> 01:32:33,861
[Prisoner screams in Italian]

1138
01:32:35,229 --> 01:32:36,628
[Gunfire]

1139
01:32:50,470 --> 01:32:52,427
[Gunfire]

1140
01:33:04,991 --> 01:33:06,903
[Clicks]

1141
01:33:06,992 --> 01:33:08,948
[Speaking German]

1142
01:33:12,911 --> 01:33:14,868
[Speaking German]

1143
01:34:19,037 --> 01:34:20,948
[Softly] Shoot me.

1144
01:34:36,357 --> 01:34:38,313
[Weber gasping]

1145
01:36:15,364 --> 01:36:17,355
He's alive.

1146
01:36:22,045 --> 01:36:23,239
MANDRAS: He's alive.

1147
01:36:23,325 --> 01:36:24,599
[Breathing heavily]

1148
01:36:24,685 --> 01:36:26,642
He was alive when I found him.

1149
01:36:35,966 --> 01:36:38,480
Fragments of uniform
in the bullet holes.

1150
01:36:38,566 --> 01:36:41,035
-Splinters of rib.
-Just do it.

1151
01:36:41,127 --> 01:36:42,765
I am not a surgeon.
I have no penicillin.

1152
01:36:42,847 --> 01:36:43,995
Please!

1153
01:36:44,086 --> 01:36:45,917
I have no sterile water.
No serum.

1154
01:36:46,006 --> 01:36:47,360
Please, Father, do it!

1155
01:37:02,768 --> 01:37:04,679
Hold.

1156
01:37:21,529 --> 01:37:23,998
IANNIS:
Four of his ribs are broken.

1157
01:37:46,371 --> 01:37:48,327
[Gasping]

1158
01:37:48,411 --> 01:37:51,688
Papa! Antonio. Don't move.

1159
01:37:51,772 --> 01:37:53,444
Don't move!

1160
01:37:53,532 --> 01:37:56,170
If you even try to move,
you will haemorrhage to death.

1161
01:37:56,251 --> 01:37:57,730
Uhh!

1162
01:37:57,811 --> 01:37:59,450
No, you must lie still.

1163
01:37:59,532 --> 01:38:04,526
How--I don't--I don't...

1164
01:38:04,612 --> 01:38:08,128
You were lying
under Carlo's body.

1165
01:38:08,213 --> 01:38:12,603
If it wasn't for him,
you wouldn't be alive.

1166
01:38:16,853 --> 01:38:18,844
How did I get here?

1167
01:38:22,534 --> 01:38:24,205
Mandras found you.

1168
01:38:38,094 --> 01:38:43,806
PELAGIA: Antonio, you
should try and drink something.

1169
01:38:43,895 --> 01:38:45,294
Antonio?

1170
01:39:14,217 --> 01:39:17,290
What would you like for lunch?

1171
01:39:17,378 --> 01:39:19,812
Not that there
is any choice, of course.

1172
01:39:19,898 --> 01:39:21,774
But if there was...

1173
01:39:27,538 --> 01:39:35,218
We needed something--
steel, wire--to bind the bones.

1174
01:39:35,298 --> 01:39:40,737
Of course, they'll have to be
removed sometime in the future.

1175
01:39:40,819 --> 01:39:44,937
I could try and get some
new strings from somewhere.

1176
01:39:45,019 --> 01:39:47,090
I could ask around.

1177
01:40:40,223 --> 01:40:41,417
Antonio!

1178
01:40:42,904 --> 01:40:44,576
What are you doing?

1179
01:40:44,664 --> 01:40:46,336
CORELLI: If they find me,
they will shoot you both.

1180
01:40:46,424 --> 01:40:48,300
They'll kill you
if you leave this house.

1181
01:40:48,383 --> 01:40:51,774
I don't belong here, Pelagia!
I never belonged here!

1182
01:40:51,864 --> 01:40:56,335
Ever since I came, look what
has happened all around you.

1183
01:40:56,424 --> 01:40:58,097
I love you.

1184
01:40:58,185 --> 01:40:59,504
I had no right
to make you love me...

1185
01:40:59,585 --> 01:41:01,540
when you weren't mine to love.

1186
01:41:03,184 --> 01:41:04,982
WOMAN: No! Don't do that!

1187
01:41:05,065 --> 01:41:06,783
[Speaking German]

1188
01:41:06,865 --> 01:41:09,857
[Speaking Italian]

1189
01:41:09,945 --> 01:41:12,141
[Speaking German]

1190
01:41:12,226 --> 01:41:15,422
-[Door opens]
-Lemoni.

1191
01:41:15,505 --> 01:41:17,894
PELAGIA: Lemoni!

1192
01:41:17,985 --> 01:41:19,305
Go to Doctor Iannis's house.

1193
01:41:19,386 --> 01:41:20,535
Go now. Go!

1194
01:41:20,626 --> 01:41:21,854
[Speaking German]

1195
01:41:21,946 --> 01:41:23,174
Go now!

1196
01:41:24,266 --> 01:41:25,460
Mama will be back!

1197
01:41:28,067 --> 01:41:29,216
[Speaking German]

1198
01:41:29,306 --> 01:41:30,739
[Gunshot]

1199
01:42:04,789 --> 01:42:07,667
[Glass breaking]

1200
01:42:07,749 --> 01:42:09,945
[Men speaking German]

1201
01:42:30,231 --> 01:42:31,710
[Doors slam]

1202
01:42:42,631 --> 01:42:46,591
Dimitris will row you
to a boat out in the bay.

1203
01:42:50,512 --> 01:42:52,947
MANDRAS: You should be home
by tomorrow night.

1204
01:42:57,792 --> 01:42:59,749
[Truck door slams]

1205
01:43:03,473 --> 01:43:05,429
[Engine starts]

1206
01:43:27,595 --> 01:43:29,267
We must go.

1207
01:43:31,315 --> 01:43:33,271
[Sobbing]

1208
01:43:42,916 --> 01:43:47,467
I had to see you again.
One last time.

1209
01:43:47,556 --> 01:43:49,195
We must go!

1210
01:43:51,597 --> 01:43:53,268
Pelagia--

1211
01:43:53,356 --> 01:43:55,825
Don't say anything.

1212
01:44:01,997 --> 01:44:03,272
Look at me.

1213
01:44:03,358 --> 01:44:04,586
DIMITRIS: We must go!

1214
01:44:04,678 --> 01:44:06,588
-Go.
-Pelagia.

1215
01:44:06,677 --> 01:44:08,827
Go! Go.

1216
01:44:31,600 --> 01:44:33,556
[Door opens]

1217
01:44:50,920 --> 01:44:54,277
Why did you save him?

1218
01:44:54,361 --> 01:44:56,750
Why didn't you
leave him to die?

1219
01:44:58,961 --> 01:45:01,430
I wanted you
to love me again.

1220
01:45:08,122 --> 01:45:14,756
In Albania, I made them read
every one of these to me.

1221
01:45:14,843 --> 01:45:18,152
"Mandras, I love you.
Mandras, I want you.

1222
01:45:18,242 --> 01:45:21,360
"Mandras, when are you
coming back?"

1223
01:45:25,683 --> 01:45:27,878
And then one day
a different letter.

1224
01:45:33,043 --> 01:45:36,400
"I don't know how
to describe my feelings.

1225
01:45:36,484 --> 01:45:38,520
"It's as if I've been
waiting a hundred years...

1226
01:45:38,604 --> 01:45:40,276
"to hear from you.

1227
01:45:40,364 --> 01:45:42,925
"Waiting a hundred years
for you to return.

1228
01:45:43,005 --> 01:45:46,440
"Once I thought
my heart was overflowing...

1229
01:45:46,524 --> 01:45:49,482
"with love for you.

1230
01:45:49,564 --> 01:45:52,602
"But now all I feel
is emptiness.

1231
01:45:52,685 --> 01:45:57,965
"And I think all the time
it was a pretence...

1232
01:45:58,046 --> 01:46:00,116
"that I never loved you at all."

1233
01:46:21,407 --> 01:46:22,840
I'm sorry.

1234
01:46:28,848 --> 01:46:30,644
I'm sorry.

1235
01:46:48,129 --> 01:46:53,761
IANNIS: The war we thought
would never end is over.

1236
01:46:53,849 --> 01:46:59,560
And the island we thought we
had lost forever is ours again.

1237
01:47:06,810 --> 01:47:11,646
In the doctor's house
there are three of us now...

1238
01:47:11,731 --> 01:47:16,247
the doctor, his daughter...

1239
01:47:16,331 --> 01:47:18,526
who is training
to be a doctor...

1240
01:47:18,611 --> 01:47:20,203
and Lemoni.

1241
01:47:20,291 --> 01:47:22,486
Pelagia! Pelagia!

1242
01:47:25,012 --> 01:47:26,763
It's for you.

1243
01:47:28,011 --> 01:47:29,524
From ltaly.

1244
01:47:51,494 --> 01:47:53,610
LEMONI: What is it?

1245
01:47:57,893 --> 01:47:59,850
It's a record.

1246
01:48:19,575 --> 01:48:22,534
[Guitar music playing]

1247
01:48:40,096 --> 01:48:41,894
[Music stops]

1248
01:48:41,977 --> 01:48:46,255
We should start making supper,
that's what we should do.

1249
01:48:46,337 --> 01:48:47,531
Lemoni.

1250
01:48:56,178 --> 01:48:59,693
IANNIS:
Antonio, I do not know...

1251
01:48:59,778 --> 01:49:01,928
if this letter
will reach you...

1252
01:49:02,018 --> 01:49:05,534
or even if you are alive.

1253
01:49:05,619 --> 01:49:08,815
Perhaps someone else
sent us your record...

1254
01:49:08,898 --> 01:49:11,538
and that is why
we found no note.

1255
01:49:13,859 --> 01:49:16,737
I would like to say
that Pelagia is happy...

1256
01:49:16,819 --> 01:49:21,097
but she is full of tears
she will not let fall...

1257
01:49:21,179 --> 01:49:26,049
and of a grief
no doctor can mend.

1258
01:49:26,140 --> 01:49:30,292
She blames herself for
the pain we have suffered...

1259
01:49:30,380 --> 01:49:33,453
and perhaps the same
is true for you.

1260
01:49:35,060 --> 01:49:38,815
You know I am not
a religious man...

1261
01:49:38,901 --> 01:49:41,734
but I believe this...

1262
01:49:41,821 --> 01:49:45,895
if there is a wound,
we must try to heal it...

1263
01:49:45,982 --> 01:49:50,099
if there is someone
whose pain we can cure...

1264
01:49:50,181 --> 01:49:53,413
we must search
till we find them...

1265
01:49:53,502 --> 01:49:57,495
if the gods have chosen
that we should survive...

1266
01:49:57,582 --> 01:49:59,538
it will be for a reason.

1267
01:52:00,670 --> 01:52:02,627
[Sobbing]

1268
01:52:16,832 --> 01:52:18,788
[Singing in Greek]

1269
01:52:55,674 --> 01:52:57,744
Where is your miracle
today then, eh?

1270
01:52:57,834 --> 01:53:00,144
What do we have
to say about that?

1271
01:53:01,555 --> 01:53:03,511
[Cheering]

1272
01:53:05,235 --> 01:53:07,192
[Greek music playing]

1273
01:53:38,917 --> 01:53:40,953
STAMATIS: Wake up.
Fetch the firewood.

1274
01:53:41,038 --> 01:53:43,393
Fix the roof.
Paint the house.

1275
01:53:43,478 --> 01:53:46,356
She's driving me mad.

1276
01:53:46,438 --> 01:53:49,954
When I was deaf,
I couldn't hear her...nagging.

1277
01:53:50,039 --> 01:53:52,188
But now--

1278
01:53:52,278 --> 01:53:56,431
Iatre, I beg of you, help me.

1279
01:53:56,519 --> 01:53:59,238
Put the pea back in my ear.

1280
01:53:59,319 --> 01:54:01,196
Iatre?

1281
01:54:08,279 --> 01:54:10,794
Lemoni?

1282
01:54:10,880 --> 01:54:13,394
Lemoni?

1283
01:54:13,480 --> 01:54:15,072
Lemoni?

1284
01:54:42,642 --> 01:54:44,758
I was looking for Lemoni.

1285
01:54:44,842 --> 01:54:47,835
She's down the road.

1286
01:54:47,923 --> 01:54:51,710
I went to the house.

1287
01:54:51,802 --> 01:54:55,239
It doesn't exist anymore.

1288
01:54:55,323 --> 01:54:57,757
We are building a new one.

1289
01:54:59,564 --> 01:55:01,680
Your father wrote
you got the record.

1290
01:55:03,883 --> 01:55:07,763
It's a guitar.
It's different.

1291
01:55:17,045 --> 01:55:19,558
I tried to live without you.

1292
01:55:19,644 --> 01:55:24,799
I tried to make myself believe
I could live without you.

1293
01:55:41,486 --> 01:55:43,239
The scar healed well.

1294
01:55:59,688 --> 01:56:04,637
Stamatis, do you love your wife?

1295
01:56:04,728 --> 01:56:09,802
If you love your wife,
my advice is be nice to her.

1296
01:56:09,888 --> 01:56:13,325
Bring in the wood
before she asks you for it.

1297
01:56:13,409 --> 01:56:18,722
If she is cold, then put
a shawl around her shoulders.

1298
01:56:18,809 --> 01:56:20,606
And bring her a flower...

1299
01:56:20,689 --> 01:56:23,157
every time you come back
from the field.

1300
01:56:23,249 --> 01:56:26,526
STAMATIS: You won't put the pea
back in my ear?

1301
01:56:26,610 --> 01:56:28,680
IANNIS: Oh, no, no, no.

1302
01:56:28,769 --> 01:56:31,886
That would be against
the Hippocratic Oath.

